  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT283-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">talaimakaṉ poruḷvayiṉ pirintavaḻi āṟṟāḷ eṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻikku “avar piriya
          āṟṟēṉ āyiṉēṉ allēṉ avar pōyiṉa kāṉattut taṉmai niṉaintu vēṟuppaṭṭēṉ” eṉṟu kiḻatti
          colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER [with the words] “As he separates I have
          not been one who has not the strength; I have changed at the thought of the kind of forest
          he has gone into.”, to the confidante who was anxious she would not have the strength when
          HE separated because of wealth. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT283">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> uḷḷatu citaippō ruḷareṉap paṭāa</l>
          <l> rillōr vāḻkkai yiraviṉu miḷiveṉac</l>
          <l> colliya vaṉmai teḷiyak kāṭṭic</l>
          <l> ceṉṟaṉar vāḻi tōḻi yeṉṟuṅ</l>
          <l> kūṟṟat taṉṉa kolaivēṉ maṟava</l>
          <l> rāṟṟirun talki vaḻaṅkunarc cekutta</l>
          <l> paṭumuṭai paruntupārt tirukku</l>
          <l> neṭumū tiṭaiya nīri lāṟē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>He went, oh friend,</l>
          <l>after he had clearly shown [his] strength, which said </l>
          <l rend="indent2">“more disgraceful than begging is a livelihood in the house</l>
          <l rend="indent2">by those who are not entitled , since they are wasters</l>
          <l rend="indent9">of what is there.” </l>
          <l rend="indent">– along the waterless paths, long [and] old ways ,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">where kites are perched [and] look out for flesh, coming up</l>
          <l rend="indent3">as the bold ones with spears always murderous</l>
          <l rend="indent6">like the god of death</l>
          <l rend="indent2">lay in wait on the way [and] kill wanderers.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
